{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Hold a UK-wide review of student loans",
        "additional_details": "We think the government and universities should protect future students and ensure financial justice.\r\n \r\nWe think there are a range of issues, and disparities. We think it is a UK-wide economic issue. PhD loans are not available now in NI. We consider that current regulation has failed. Terms of loans change. We demand a UK review. We want this to look at costs, postcode inequality, rule changes, and accountability.",
        "background": "We want a UK-wide review of the student loan system, and university accountability. Students paid full fees for disrupted education during the pandemic. Across the UK there are funding inequalities, and we think the loan terms are unfair. ",
